                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-lg text-gray-100 font-semibold">
                  Built for teams
                </h4>
                <p class="mt-3">
                  Built for teams, by a team. We know what you need, and Shlef
                  delivers on that promise.
                </p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="py-14 bg-gray-800" id="faq">
      <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-4 gap-12 md:flex md:px-8">
        <div class="flex-1">
          <div class="max-w-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-cyan-400">
              Frequently asked questions
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-white text-3xl font-extrabold sm:text-4xl">
              All the information you need to know, and more.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 mt-12 md:mt-0">
          <ul class="space-y-4 divide-y divide-gray-700">
            <li class="py-5">
              <summary
                class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-gray-200"
              >
                Why create Shlef?
              </summary>
              <p class="mt-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                File privacy is a big issue. We believe that privacy is a right,
                and not a feature. That's why we created Shlef. To give you the
                power to share files with your team, without having to worry
                about your data being sold to third-parties. Because that is
                just plain wrong.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="py-5">
              <summary
                class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-gray-200"
              >
                How does Shlef work?
              </summary>
              <p class="mt-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                Shlef is a self-hosted file sharing platform, built with
                security in mind. Self-hosted means that Shlef is hosted
                locally, so that your data never leaves your network. This keeps
                your data safe and secure.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li class="py-5">
              <summary
                class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-gray-200"
              >
                How do I get started?
              </summary>
              <p class="mt-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                Shlef isn't production ready yet, but we're working hard to get
                it out there. In the meantime, why not check out our
                <a
                  href="https://github.com/shlef/"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="text-sky-500 hover:text-sky-400 duration-150">GitHub</a
                >?
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
